              <title>OCWC Global 2011: University California Irvine 10 reasons for OCW</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5434</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5434</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Larry Cooperman and Gary Matkin - run through the reasons they have found for UCI to adopt OCW:</p>
<p><ol>
<li>Serve current students</li>
<li>Attract new students</li>
<li>Support faculty</li>
<li>Facilitate accountability and continuous improvement</li>
<li>Advance institutional recognition</li>
<li>Support public service role</li>
<li>Disseminate results of research and attract research students</li>
<li>Serve as a repository of digital assets</li>
<li>Serve learning communities (of all types)</li>
<li>Enhance international service and reputation</li>
</ol>
<div>Trying to behave something else - flag up future experience rather than necessarily a "course". &nbsp;The other side is what to do to get buy in from the university:</div>
<div><ol>
<li>A website to be proud of</li>
<li>Help students and facult</li>
<li>Leverage and support existing units</li>
<li>Build an inventory - and spread it around</li>
<li>Create miro demonstrations and publicise them</li>
<li>Get media attention internal and external</li>
</ol></div>
