              <title>OER 2011 Rapid Fire: Jim Shelton, Assistant Deputy Secretary for Innovation and Improvement, U.S. Department of Education</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5248</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5248</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>A four step approach was described:</p>
<ol>
<li>~$0 is &ldquo;almost&rdquo; inevitable but Sub Optimal Educational Resouces dominate rather than true OER</li>
<li>More and better OER about creating effective ER &ndash; design thinking</li>
<li>Provide better tools/reduce barriers to quality</li>
<li>Create a better context/align incentives</li>
</ol>
<p>Free makes it easier to adopt and innovate.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
