              <title>University College London: Open Learning Environment for Early Modern Low Countries History</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3209</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3209</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>This project is JISC and Higher Education Academy &nbsp;funded, and aims to turn a comprehensive survey course in Early Modern Low Countries history, from the late Middle Ages to the end of the 18th century, into a multimedia and Web 2.0 enriched Open Educational Resource (OER).&nbsp;</p>
<p>It makes available existing teaching materials from the proposer&rsquo;s survey course in early Low Countries history, DUTC1011&nbsp;<em style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Aspects of the history of the Low Countries,&nbsp;</em>which is currently taught as a web-enhanced face-to-face course to undergraduate students at UCL.</p>
<p>Type of initiative: subject specific</p>
<p>Funding runs from 30th April 2009- 30th April 2010</p>]]></description>
